1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,300
<i>If you saw him,
you'd realize it's not him.</i>

2
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:03,933
<i> I have to do something.</i>

3
00:00:04,067 --> 00:00:06,100
<i>- Do you love Snoop?
- No.</i>

4
00:00:06,267 --> 00:00:07,200
<i> Just concerned.</i>

5
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:09,067
<i> You deserve this.</i>

6
00:00:09,167 --> 00:00:11,967
<i>It's not even enough after
what you've done to my family.</i>

7
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:13,900
<i>I just wanted
to see you locked up.</i>

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,400
<i>You said you'd give me
whatever I'd ask for.</i>

9
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,600
<i>Yes. As long as you
sell GLC back to me.</i>

10
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:23,767
<i>Withdraw the lawsuit against
my mom, Snoop, and Sherwin.</i>

11
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,367
<i> Make sure they'll be set free.</i>

12
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,633
<i>Is this the end?
Are we giving up?</i>

13
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:30,100
<i>Please.
We'll make this work, right?</i>

14
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:32,267
<i>We're unbreakable.
Bingo, please.</i>

15
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,933
<i>- Come inside.
- Bingo.</i>

16
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:35,800
<i> Charleston.</i>

17
00:00:35,967 --> 00:00:39,467
[SOBBING]

18
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,633
So what's the game plan, Wilson?

19
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,400
<i>To buy everything back
from Bingo,</i>

20
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:50,133
<i>we need a partnership
with the Tanhuecos.</i>

21
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,467
<i> Caroline.</i>

22
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:54,833
<i> The future of the family...</i>

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,567
<i> is now in your hands.</i>

24
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:03,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

25
00:01:52,233 --> 00:01:55,633
[BINGO] I feel like I'm drowning
in embarrassment.

26
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,300
[SIGHS]

27
00:02:00,167 --> 00:02:02,167
But I did the right thing,
didn't I?

28
00:02:04,033 --> 00:02:05,967
To put an end to all of this.

29
00:02:08,533 --> 00:02:10,633
My mother is
a wicked person, right?

30
00:02:11,267 --> 00:02:12,567
Right, Papi?

31
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:14,667
Grandma?

32
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,100
She ordered a kidnapping.

33
00:02:17,233 --> 00:02:18,667
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

34
00:02:18,767 --> 00:02:20,933
She sought revenge
against the Tius.

35
00:02:22,367 --> 00:02:24,733
And those Tius are evil, too.

36
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:28,333
They were backing me
into a corner.

37
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,833
They even dragged Snoop into it!

38
00:02:30,933 --> 00:02:32,400
- [GLASS BREAKS]
- Snoop!

39
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:36,833
It wasn't our fight
in the first place!

40
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:40,000
So, why are we
the ones suffering?

41
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:42,733
Take a seat. Calm down.

42
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:51,533
[FRUSTRATED SIGH]

43
00:02:53,267 --> 00:02:54,933
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

44
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:03,533
I know it's hurting Ling,
Grandma.

45
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:12,400
I don't want that.

46
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:16,767
I can't take it.

47
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:23,467
And now, I don't know.

48
00:03:25,533 --> 00:03:27,467
I don't know what to do.

49
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:33,600
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

50
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:41,800
That's right, Bingo.

51
00:03:43,133 --> 00:03:44,833
Go ahead and vent it out.

52
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,567
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

53
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:50,733
After that, go and talk to Ling.

54
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:55,667
You may not know
what to do right now,

55
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,867
but it will come to you
eventually.

56
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,633
Let your feelings guide you.

57
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:19,467
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

58
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:30,900
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

59
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:42,000
I know it's too early
for a drink, but...

60
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:44,000
Cheers, brother. We did it.

61
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:45,567
[CHARLESTON SIGHS]

62
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:50,367
Remember, Carlo, what we did...

63
00:04:52,067 --> 00:04:53,633
we did it for the family.

64
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:56,967
[CLINKS]

65
00:04:57,067 --> 00:05:03,467
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:41,633
- [ENGINE TURNS OFF]
- [DOOR OPENS]

67
00:06:01,567 --> 00:06:03,033
Now, can we talk?

68
00:06:10,767 --> 00:06:13,900
In a calmer and
more rationale manner?

69
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,500
I'm embarrassed to face you...

70
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:38,233
...to be honest...

71
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,067
...because of what
my mother did.

72
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:47,100
Bingo.

73
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:52,267
We're not going to talk
about your mother.

74
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,133
Because you are not your mom.

75
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:01,967
Whatever she did back then,
it shouldn't concern us.

76
00:07:02,133 --> 00:07:05,133
- We can't let it affect us.
- But it does affect me.

77
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:08,967
And it affects you, too.

78
00:07:10,967 --> 00:07:12,633
Bingo, I'm here

79
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,967
because I want to know
if we're still okay.

80
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,567
That's what matters, right?

81
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:25,300
And that's the only thing
I want to talk about,

82
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:27,233
ff we're still going to fight.

83
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:32,900
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

84
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:36,800
I am selling the GLC back
to your family.

85
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,000
I already know that.

86
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,067
I am selling the GLC

87
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:50,733
so my mother's kidnapping case
will be dropped.

88
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:53,700
Did you know that, too?

89
00:07:58,533 --> 00:08:00,067
So she'll be free?

90
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,100
Why would you do that?

91
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:09,333
You just told me she did it,
and now you want her free?

92
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,167
Because, she's still
my mother, Ling.

93
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,000
She's still my mother.

94
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:17,733
What about you and your dad?

95
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,567
You readily believe
whatever he says.

96
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:23,000
Because my father is different.

97
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:27,433
You know what?

98
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:30,067
Maybe this isn't a good idea.

99
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:34,233
Different? Why?

100
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,267
Because he didn't kill your mom?

101
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:37,967
Why?

102
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,600
Your mother's the one
who killed her, right?

103
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:47,567
The truth finally came out.

104
00:08:48,567 --> 00:08:50,033
Right from the start,

105
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,267
that's what you've
always believed.

106
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:58,100
Because I'm not a saint.

107
00:09:01,100 --> 00:09:04,667
Don't I have the right
to feel this way

108
00:09:05,933 --> 00:09:08,833
since I'm the one who got hurt
by what she did?

109
00:09:11,333 --> 00:09:13,233
Why is it wrong to you?

110
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:15,067
After everything I've found out,

111
00:09:15,167 --> 00:09:17,600
I'm still not allowed
to believe it?

112
00:09:28,367 --> 00:09:29,367
[CAROLINE SIGHS]

113
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:42,433
Thank you.

114
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:46,767
Thank you.

115
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,767
Thank you, Bettina.

116
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,100
Thank you for stopping by,
Brian and Charry.

117
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,167
No worries.

118
00:09:56,333 --> 00:10:00,667
I also want to discuss
some details of the wedding.

119
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,867
I hope you don't mind
that I've chosen

120
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:05,300
a good date already, Cindy.

121
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:06,900
Of course, Charry.

122
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:10,133
Family traditions
are very important.

123
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,700
However...

124
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:21,467
would you consider Bettina

125
00:10:21,567 --> 00:10:24,033
to be part of your
family instead?

126
00:10:33,433 --> 00:10:38,700
A-- Are you saying that
she'll be Stephen's bride

127
00:10:38,867 --> 00:10:41,000
instead of Caroline?

128
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:45,100
It would be my honor
to serve both families.

129
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:50,433
I know you're a wonderful
woman, Bettina,

130
00:10:51,633 --> 00:10:55,433
and any man
will be lucky to have you.

131
00:10:55,567 --> 00:11:00,000
But we also want our son

132
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,733
to marry someone he loves.

133
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:06,833
And right now, it's Caroline.

134
00:11:06,967 --> 00:11:12,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:16,400
Are you asking us to consider
one of your daughters instead

136
00:11:16,567 --> 00:11:20,100
because Caroline didn't agree
to the arrangement?

137
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:27,867
If you really can't
convince Caroline,

138
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,567
we can forgo the wedding.

139
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:34,233
We are still willing
to invest in GLC.

140
00:11:35,233 --> 00:11:38,367
But we want it
under Stephen's name.

141
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:43,933
Uh, I'm sorry, but that
would mean Stephen

142
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,733
would be the majority
shareholder of GLC, then.

143
00:11:46,867 --> 00:11:49,733
- [BRIAN] Mm-hmm.
- Yes, because...

144
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:52,933
Because one condition
of the agreement

145
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:56,067
is Caroline marrying Stephen.

146
00:11:56,200 --> 00:12:01,300
Only then will we let you
be the majority shareholders.

147
00:12:03,267 --> 00:12:06,067
Let's adhere
to our initial agreement.

148
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:12,067
Stephen will be wed to Caroline.
I promise.

149
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,400
You'll have nothing
to worry about.

150
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,800
I don't want to believe
anything anymore...

151
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:32,500
...if it would mean...

152
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:40,133
...that I'm going to lose you.

153
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:46,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

154
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,300
I want to feel...

155
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:54,633
I want to feel
that we're still fighting.

156
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:59,133
That's what you said, right?

157
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:03,167
We're unbreakable.

158
00:13:06,167 --> 00:13:09,300
For better or for worse...

159
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:17,067
...you'll never leave me.

160
00:13:24,567 --> 00:13:25,500
[SNIFFLES]

161
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:30,233
That's enough.

162
00:13:30,933 --> 00:13:34,267
[CAROLINE SOBBING]

163
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,500
That's enough.

164
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:43,933
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

165
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:55,200
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

166
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:03,567
[SIGHS]

167
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:04,700
Wilson.

168
00:14:05,567 --> 00:14:08,067
You promised Caroline
to the Tanhuecos

169
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:10,700
when you haven't
even convinced her yet.

170
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,567
I have to, Cindy.

171
00:14:12,733 --> 00:14:16,900
With that, the GLC will still
remain in the family.

172
00:14:17,067 --> 00:14:20,200
But, Papa, how are you going
to convince Caroline?

173
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:23,033
She's so in love with Bingo.

174
00:14:23,167 --> 00:14:25,033
And you know
how stubborn she is.

175
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:27,300
[ANNOYED GRUNT] That family!

176
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:31,333
If we need to solve it
for them, then fine.

177
00:14:31,467 --> 00:14:33,767
But we have to do
something, Wilson,

178
00:14:33,933 --> 00:14:36,067
because this is going
to hurt us.

179
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:46,900
There. That's what you
brought for me before, right?

180
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,300
Chicken soup
and veggie pork stew?

181
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:50,900
Yeah. You said they're
healthy dishes.

182
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:54,233
Yes, but I'm not pregnant,
you know.

183
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:56,400
Just kidding. Thank you.

184
00:14:56,533 --> 00:15:01,267
Oh, and I also have fruits
in a basket.

185
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,200
There.

186
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:04,933
Wait, isn't this the one
I gave you?

187
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:06,600
- No, that's new.
- Okay.

188
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:09,533
So you're just giving me
what I gave you before.

189
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:13,933
Well, if you want, I'll sneak in
some booze next time.

190
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:16,167
Hey, not so loud.
Someone might hear you.

191
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:19,200
Of course, I won't do that.
I'm not a dummy like you.

192
00:15:19,733 --> 00:15:25,200
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,533
How are things
at your house?

194
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,100
Oh, please don't worry
about me.

195
00:15:36,267 --> 00:15:38,667
I'm okay. I promise.

196
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:42,000
I'm not the one dealing
with a huge problem. It's you.

197
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:44,133
Well, and my sibling.

198
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:50,733
Aren't you going
to try the chicken soup?

199
00:15:50,867 --> 00:15:52,033
Try it.

200
00:15:52,167 --> 00:15:54,300
I never say no to food.

201
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,133
Even better that it's from you.

202
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:58,067
So, who made this?

203
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:00,667
Me.

204
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:02,467
- [CHUCKLES]
- If it's good.

205
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,467
- But if not, blame the maid.
- Okay.

206
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:13,700
I don't know anymore, dude.

207
00:16:14,467 --> 00:16:16,600
I think I'm just being stupid.

208
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:19,933
I'm outside the precinct
right now,

209
00:16:21,033 --> 00:16:24,833
waiting for the girl who
I'm not sure really loves me.

210
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:28,667
[CLICKS TONGUE]

211
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:33,067
Dude, you know I've liked her
since high school.

212
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:37,033
I just didn't have the guts
back then.

213
00:16:38,467 --> 00:16:40,167
But I know she's worth it.

214
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:43,900
I guess.

215
00:16:44,067 --> 00:16:45,233
[IRENE] Hey.

216
00:16:46,300 --> 00:16:49,367
- I have to go.
- Visiting hours is over.

217
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:50,967
- Are you done?
- Yeah.

218
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,267
Let's go.

219
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,400
- Aldrich.
- Yeah?

220
00:16:55,833 --> 00:16:57,967
I just want to say thank you.

221
00:16:58,567 --> 00:17:00,533
Thanks for being
so supportive.

222
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:03,733
Anything for you.

223
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,533
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

224
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:18,733
Thank you.

225
00:17:26,100 --> 00:17:27,633
I took your advice.

226
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,900
I made the decision
to set up Caroline

227
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,400
out of the love I have
for my family.

228
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,900
It's for their own good.

229
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:40,833
Are you sure?

230
00:17:42,267 --> 00:17:44,233
Are you saying it's not?

231
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:49,500
Wilson, all I'm saying is,
are you being completely honest

232
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:52,767
that you made the decision
out of that love?

233
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:55,600
If yes, then it is.

234
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:59,767
Only you can answer
your own question, Wilson.

235
00:18:02,633 --> 00:18:06,200
Why don't you just
buy our shares instead?

236
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:11,467
My business is not big enough
to acquire that, Wilson.

237
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:14,100
Maybe if it didn't cost
a lot of millions, sure.

238
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:17,367
But we're talking
about a corporation.

239
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,600
You want to get things done,

240
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,500
but you do not want
to pay the price.

241
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:27,300
That's not the way it is.

242
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:30,367
Whatever decision you make,

243
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,733
as long as it's
for the family's sake,

244
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:37,300
you must stand by it
and never regret it.

245
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:42,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

246
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,667
You shouldn't have made
that decision.

247
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:52,833
I'm fine here. You don't have
to worry about my freedom.

248
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,167
- I'm paying for--
- No matter how I look at it...

249
00:18:58,033 --> 00:18:59,667
it doesn't sit well with me.

250
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,833
It's the only solution
I could think of.

251
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:04,900
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

252
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:06,533
You're free from prison.

253
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:09,567
I'm free from the GLC.

254
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:11,767
[SNIFFLES]

255
00:19:14,433 --> 00:19:16,233
Ling and I are free.

256
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:24,600
And I also want
a quiet and simple life.

257
